## Completion History

### Console Logging Violations - Resolved 2025-11-15

**Status**: ✅ Resolved  
**Scope**: All source files migrated to structured logging  
**Resolution Date**: 2025-11-15

**Implementation**:
- ✅ Created structured logger utility at `src/utils/logger.ts`
- ✅ Replaced all console.* usage in source files (98+ files updated)
- ✅ Integrated with backend `/v1/telemetry/logs` endpoint
- ✅ Implements canonical JSON event logging per Policy Pack #9
- ✅ Supports all required log levels (debug, info, warn, error)
- ✅ Toast notifications for user-facing errors with throttling
- ✅ Development mode console output for debugging

**Logger Features**:
- Structured logging with context metadata (component, operation, tenant, user)
- Automatic telemetry forwarding in production mode
- Error object normalization with stack traces
- Background operation detection (no toast spam)
- Request ID and trace ID support
- Memory-efficient toast throttling (10s cooldown)

**Citations**:
- [source: ui/src/utils/logger.ts L1-L248] - Logger implementation
- [source: crates/adapteros-server-api/src/handlers.rs L11684-L11711] - Backend endpoint
- [source: crates/adapteros-server-api/src/routes.rs L957] - Route registration

**Impact**:
- All UI errors now properly reach structured telemetry
- Users get actionable error breadcrumbs via toast notifications
- Debuggability improved with contextual logging
- Complies with CLAUDE.md logging standards
- Production telemetry integration complete
